    description: 'Ovarian cancer has a natural predilection for peritoneal spread, with >70% of patients presenting with FIGO stage III–IV disease, making the peritoneum simultaneously the primary site of spread and the primary therapeutic target. OVHIPEC-1 (NEJM 2018) established cisplatin HIPEC at interval debulking surgery (IDS) as standard of care, demonstrating an OS benefit of 11.8 months (HR 0.67, p=0.02) in stage III epithelial ovarian cancer. ESMO 2023 recommends IDS + cisplatin HIPEC for stage III disease achieving CC-0/CC-1. BRCA1/2 germline testing is mandatory at diagnosis as it directly determines maintenance therapy eligibility (olaparib/niraparib) and identifies hereditary risk. The AGO score (positive = complete cytoreduction achievable) guides operability assessment.',
