    systemic_treatment: 'Histotype-specific (ESMO Sarcoma Guidelines 2023): DDLPS: doxorubicin ± ifosfamide 1L; trabectedin 2L (L-sarcoma trial: PFS 5.6 vs 1.5 months vs BSC); eribulin (L-sarcoma subset, OS benefit). LMS: gemcitabine+docetaxel; trabectedin; pazopanib. GIST: imatinib 400mg/day 1L (3 years adjuvant for high-risk); sunitinib 2L; regorafenib 3L; ripretinib 4L (INVICTUS: PFS 6.3 vs 1.0 months); avapritinib (PDGFRA D842V, NAVIGATOR: 91% ORR). Solitary fibrous tumour: bevacizumab+temozolomide (Stacchiotti regimen). MPNST with NF1: MEK inhibitor (selumetinib).',
    follow_up: 'CT every 3–4 months for 2 years. For GIST: FDG-PET for imatinib response monitoring (Choi criteria on CT: density change ≥15% or size decrease ≥10%). LDH (non-specific). Clinical examination. Duration: 10 years for RPS (late recurrences are common — WDLPS median time to local recurrence >5 years). WDLPS: surveillance CT every 6 months (local recurrence dominant pattern, re-resect). LMS: CT chest (lung metastases dominant — every 3 months for 2 years).',
    prognosis: 'Depends entirely on histological subtype. GIST with peritoneal disease: median OS 6+ years with imatinib; peritoneal relapse rate 50% at 5 years without adjuvant imatinib. DDLPS local peritoneal recurrence: median OS 18–36 months; re-resection feasible in selected cases. LMS peritoneal: median OS 12–24 months (distant recurrence dominant). WDLPS pure: essentially cannot metastasise; re-resect local recurrences repeatedly. STRASS (EORTC 62092, Lancet Oncol 2020): preoperative RT benefit in WDLPS/DDLPS subgroup only (ARFS HR 0.67) — only RCT in RPS history.',
    clinical_pearls: [
      'GIST is the peritoneal sarcomatosis histotype where systemic therapy (imatinib) provides durable disease control — operate after achieving maximum response (6–12 months), not upfront. Avapritinib for PDGFRA D842V mutant achieves 91% ORR and is completely imatinib-resistant.',
      'Histotype drives everything in sarcoma — WDLPS recurs locally (re-resect repeatedly; essentially cannot metastasise), LMS recurs distantly (systemic therapy priority, lung surveillance critical). Never conflate these two in management.',
      'MDM2 FISH/IHC is mandatory for all retroperitoneal tumours — it definitively distinguishes WDLPS/DDLPS (MDM2 amplified) from benign lipoma (MDM2 negative). Lipomas >10 cm in the retroperitoneum are WDLPS until proven otherwise.',
      'Peritoneal sarcomatosis is NOT equivalent to carcinomatosis — HIPEC evidence from CRC or ovarian cancer does not translate to sarcoma. Doxorubicin IP remains investigational. Do not offer CRS+HIPEC for sarcomatosis outside expert centres and clinical trial frameworks.',
      'STRASS (Lancet Oncol 2020) is the only RCT in retroperitoneal sarcoma history. It evaluated preoperative radiotherapy (NOT chemotherapy) — no benefit overall, but WDLPS/DDLPS subgroup showed ARFS benefit (HR 0.67). STRASS2 evaluates preoperative doxorubicin+ifosfamide in high-grade RPS.',
      'PDGFRA D842V-mutant GIST (5% of all GIST): completely imatinib-resistant. Avapritinib (type I kinase inhibitor, NAVIGATOR trial) achieves 91% ORR — mutation-specific testing at diagnosis is mandatory for all GIST.',
    ],
    tags: ['sarcomatosis', 'GIST', 'liposarcoma', 'DDLPS', 'WDLPS', 'LMS', 'DSRCT', 'MDM2', 'CDK4', 'imatinib', 'avapritinib', 'doxorubicin', 'retroperitoneal', 'TARPSWG', 'STRASS', 'ESMO-sarcoma'],
