    pipac_indication: 'PIPAC for unresectable SBA-PM: oxaliplatin 92 mg/m² (extrapolated from CRC PIPAC protocol). Case reports and very small series only. Theoretical rationale based on shared molecular biology with CRC. Consider if systemic therapy fails or patient not fit for CRS.',
    systemic_treatment: '5-FU/LV or capecitabine-based regimens. FOLFOX or CAPOX as 1L extrapolated from CRC (NCCN recommends CRC-based regimens for SBA). HER2+ SBA: trastuzumab (extrapolated from gastric HER2+ data). MSI-H: pembrolizumab 1L (KEYNOTE-177 data extrapolated — SBA not separately enrolled). BALLAD trial (capecitabine ± bevacizumab after resection): DFS trend, not OS benefit confirmed. Clinical trial preferred given rarity.',
