    staging: 'No validated AJCC staging system for DSRCT. Research staging: Stage I = localised resectable, II = localised unresectable or limited peritoneal, III = disseminated peritoneal ± LN, IV = extra-abdominal metastases (liver, lung, bone). Virtually all patients present Stage II–III. Staging evaluation: CT chest/abdomen/pelvis + FDG-PET + bone scan (or whole-body FDG-PET replaces conventional scintigraphy). Liver metastases present in ~30% at diagnosis — adverse prognostic factor.',
    patient_selection: 'Aggressive multimodal protocol at specialist centre. Eligibility for aggressive surgical debulking (≥90% cytoreduction): PS ECOG 0–1, age <40 (relative), no/minimal extra-abdominal metastases (liver metastases are adverse but not absolute contraindication at some centres), response to neoadjuvant P6 chemotherapy (assess by FDG-PET after 2–3 cycles), surgical team with DSRCT experience. HIPEC: not standard — used at select expert centres (MSKCC, MD Anderson, European centres) within compassionate framework or prospective registry. Goal is >90% cytoreduction (R1 acceptable over leaving large deposits). WART available at limited centres.',
