    staging: 'FIGO 2014 staging (same as ovarian cancer): all patients stage III+ by definition since ovaries are minimally involved and disease is diffusely peritoneal. M0 if no distant metastases (stage IIIC most common). Pathological confirmation of ovarian non-involvement (<5mm) required for PPC designation — this is a histological criterion.',
    patient_selection: 'Identical to ovarian cancer ESMO 2023 criteria: ECOG 0–1, complete/partial response to NACT × 3 cycles carboplatin+paclitaxel, technical feasibility of CC-0/CC-1, no parenchymal liver metastases, no extensive upper abdominal disease precluding CC-0. PPC was included in OVHIPEC-1 trial — outcomes similar to HGSOC in subgroup analyses. Apply cisplatin HIPEC (100 mg/m², 40°C, 90 min) at interval debulking surgery as per OVHIPEC-1 protocol. BRCA testing before surgery to guide maintenance therapy.',
