    description: 'Signet ring cell carcinoma (SRCC) with peritoneal involvement represents the most aggressive subtype of peritoneal carcinomatosis across all origins (gastric, colonic, appendiceal). The poorly cohesive carcinoma phenotype (diffuse infiltration, absent stroma-reaction, rapid transcoelomic spread) accounts for universally poor outcomes despite aggressive surgical approaches, and CRS+HIPEC is explicitly contraindicated in most ESMO 2023, ASCO, and PSOGI guidelines. The linitis plastica growth pattern creates the illusion of limited disease on CT imaging when microscopic peritoneal infiltration is already extensive. Systemic therapy guided by molecular profiling (CLDN18.2, HER2, MSI, PD-L1) combined with palliative PIPAC for ascites control represents the appropriate management paradigm.',
